  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    A[Misfolded Protein in ER Lumen or Membrane] --> B[ER Stress Signal Activation (e.g., UPR)]\n    B --> C{Is Misfolded Protein Luminal or Membrane Substrate?}\n\n    C -->|Luminal| D[Luminal Misfold Recognition Pathway (ERAD-L)]\n    D --> E[BiP/Hsp70 Chaperone Binding]\n    E --> F[Sec63/Lhs1 J-domain Protein Interaction]\n    F --> G[PDI Family Protein Interaction (e.g., PDI1)]\n    G --> H[Misfolded Protein-Chaperone Complex Formed]\n    H --> I[Hrd3 ERAD Receptor Recruitment to Complex]\n    I --> J[Hrd3-Hrd1 E3 Ligase Interaction]\n\n    C -->|Membrane| K[Membrane Misfold Recognition Pathway (ERAD-M)]\n    K --> L[Direct Misfolded Protein-Hrd1 Interaction]\n    L --> M[Der1 ERAD Receptor Involvement]\n    M --> N[Usa1 Recruitment to Hrd1/Der1 Complex]\n\n    J --> O_AND{\"Hrd1 Retrotranslocon Complex Assembled?\"}\n    N --> O_AND\n\n    O_AND --> P[Sec61 Translocon Channel Engagement]\n    P --> Q[Sec61 Luminal Loop 4 Role in Substrate Engagement (Wheeler MC, 2012)]\n\n    O_AND --> R[E1 Ubiquitin Activating Enzyme (Uba1) Action]\n    R --> S[\"Ubiquitin Activation: Ub-AMP formation\"]\n    S --> T[E2 Ubiquitin Conjugating Enzyme (Ubc7/Ubc1) Recruitment]\n    T --> U[Ubiquitin Transfer to E2 (E2~Ub Thioester)]\n    U --> V[E2 Chemoselectivity & Linkage Specificity (Swarnkar A, 2024)]\n\n    Q --> W[Hrd1 E3 Ligase Catalysis of Ub Transfer]\n    V --> W\n\n    W --> X[Initial Ubiquitination of Misfolded Protein]\n    X --> Y[Polyubiquitin Chain Elongation (K48-linked)]\n    Y --> Z[Polyubiquitinated Misfolded Protein (ER lumen/membrane)]\n\n    Z --> AA[CDC48/Ufd1/Npl4 AAA-ATPase Complex Recruitment]\n    AA --> AB[CDC48 ATP Binding & Hydrolysis Cycle]\n    AB --> AC[Mechanical Pulling of Substrate into Cytosol]\n    AC --> AD[Dislocated Polyubiquitinated Protein in Cytosol]\n\n    AD --> AE[Png1 N-glycanase Action (Deglycosylation)]\n    AE --> AF[Deglycosylated, Polyubiquitinated Protein]\n    AF --> AG[\"Deubiquitinating Enzymes (DUBs: Doa4, Ubp3) Activity\"]\n    AG --> AH[Targeted Protein for 26S Proteasome]\n    AH --> AI[26S Proteasome Recruitment & Cap Interaction]\n    AI --> AJ[Proteasomal Substrate Entry & Unfolding]\n    AJ --> AK[/Proteasomal Degradation into Peptides/]\n\n    AK --> AL[Peptides & Amino Acids]\n    AK --> AM[Recycled Ubiquitin]\n    AK --> AN[Recycled CDC48/Ufd1/Npl4 Complex]\n    AK --> AO[Recycled E2 Enzymes (Ubc7/Ubc1)]\n    AK --> AP[Recycled Hrd1 Complex Components]\n\n    AL & AM & AN & AO & AP --> AQ[ERAD Process Complete & ER Homeostasis Restored]\n\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style G fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style H fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style K fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style L fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style M fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style N fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AND fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style P fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Q fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style R fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style S fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style T fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style U fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style E2 fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style X fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style Y fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Z fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AA fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AB fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AD fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AF fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AG fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AH fill:#ffa726,color:#fff